description:
Come and enjoy a wonderful New York experience in this beautiful Upper East Side haven! Everything you could possibly need in walking distance including trains, grocery stores, restaurants, bars, famous museums and landmarks, not to mention Central Park is only minutes away!

*Fully Furnished 
*Flat Screen Sony TV
*High Speed WIFI
*Netflix, Hulu, Amazon Video & Many More Apps
*Exposed Brick Wall & Fireplace
*Beautiful Art From Around the World
*Large Living Room with Sofa Bed
*Great Closet Space
*Brand New Comfortable Queen Sized Bed
*Seating Area
*Music Speaker to Connect to Any Device
*Kitchen Equipped With Plenty Of Pots & Pans/All Equipment Needs
*Conventional Oven, Microwave, Electric Kettle, Coffee Maker, etc...
*Large Soaking Bathtub  
*Hardwood Floors
*All Utilities Included

You'll have access to the entire apartment, the separate kitchen and bathroom as well as a large closet.

I'm more than happy to offer any recommendations and help you have a Fabulous stay in any way that I can.

This Upper East Side Gem Is Located In The Most Affluent, Beautiful & Convenient Neighborhood In Manhattan. Also the Safest Community In NYC Next To Tribeca- Welcome To The Upper East Side! 

*NYC's Premier Destination
*3 Minute Walk to Q Express Train
*7-10 Minute Walk To 4,5 & 6 Train
*Only 1 Subway Stop From 5th Ave Shopping & Christmas Displays Including Bloomingdales, Rockefeller Center & Saks Fifth Ave
*2 Quick Subway Stops From Grand Central Station
*Walk To Central Park in 10-15 Minutes 
*Walk To Gracie Mansion (Mayors Residence) in 5 Minutes
*Walking Distance To Everything You Could Possibly Need: Grocery Stores, Laundry Across The Street, Numerous Restaurants, Bars, Museums, Parks, Cafes & Coffee Shops, Nail & Hair Salons, 24/7 Pharmacies (Duane Reade), etc.
*Walk To Many Museums Including Metropolitan Museum Of Modern Art, Guggenheim & Frick
*2 Movie Theaters Including AMC Loews
*Only 1-4 Block Radius Away From Many Famous Stores Including:
Whole Foods
Fairway (Open until 1AM Daily)
Duane Reade
Shake Shack
Sephora
Best Buy
Victoria's Secret
L'Occitane
H&M
Gap
Barnes & Noble
Modells Sporting Goods
Papaya Dog
Organic Avenue
Housing Works (thrift store)
Fast Food: Papa John's Pizza, McDonalds, Dominos, Burger King
Uno Pizzeria & Chicago Grill

Personal Recommendations:
I have many personal recommendations for restaurants and activities in the area I'm happy to share. 

For Restaurants/Cafes:
La Maison du Chocolat Cafe
L'Absinthe- amazing French cuisine
Serendipity 3- Great Desserts & Celebrity Hot Spot
Infirmary- Cajun-Creole restaurant and bar less than a half block away 
La Pulperia- Latin Seafood
Pinocchio- Italian
The Mansion- Neighborhood diner
Drunken Monkey- Indian
Candle 79- Vegan Food
Sushi Para- Japanese & Chinese
Agora- Turkisk BYOB
The Writing Room- New American
Calexico- Mexican & Cocktails
Poke- Sushi

Michelin Guide Rated & Within 1-3 blocks:
San Mateo- Italian 
Uva- Italian Wine Bar tapas style and regular entrees
J.G Melon- Tavern & Famous Burgers
Beyoglu- Turkish & Mediterranean 

Budget Friendly:
Shake Shack- great burgers, fries & milkshakes
Roma's Pizza
Dos Toros Taqueria
Mamagyro
H&H Bagels
Hale & Hearty Soups
Hummus Kitchen

All You Can Eat:
Chinatown East- Japanese/Chinese unlimited food and beer, wine & sake
Brick Lane Curry House- Indian
Texas De Brazil- Brazilian Steakhouse

Happy Hours:
Just Walk Out The Apartment & Numerous Choices Within 2 Blocks From 4-7PM.

*3 Minute Walk to Q Express Train
*7-10 Minute Walk To 4,5 & 6 Train
*Only 1 Subway Stop From 5th Ave Shopping & Christmas Displays Including Bloomingdales, Rockefeller Center & Saks Fifth Ave
*2 Quick Subway Stops From Grand Central Station

Walking Distance To Everything!

hosts.about:
I'm a very outgoing and social person with a great love for travel and food! I enjoy learning about different cultures and perspectives. In my free time I host dinner parties for friends and family as I happen to be a pretty decent cook:)

My hobbies are reading, cooking, horseback riding, most outdoor activities and recently learning to fly! I don't watch much TV, but my life has greater meaning when Game Of Thrones season rolls around:)
